               <p>Second Count. Laying it to be the property of persons unknown.</p>
               <p>
            
                  <persName id="t17980523-19-person208">
                  HENRY
                   BISHOP
               <interp inst="t17980523-19-person208" type="surname" value="BISHOP"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17980523-19-person208" type="given" value="HENRY"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17980523-19-person208" type="gender" value="male"></interp>
                  </persName>
             sworn. - I am porter to Messrs. Brown and Son, <rs id="t17980523-19-viclabel99" type="occupation">proprietors of the Taunton waggon</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t17980523-19-victim201 t17980523-19-viclabel99"></join>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t17980523-19-victim203 t17980523-19-viclabel99"></join>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t17980523-19-victim205 t17980523-19-viclabel99"></join>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t17980523-19-victim207 t17980523-19-viclabel99"></join>, <placeName id="t17980523-19-crimeloc100">Saracen's-head, Friday-street</placeName>
                  <interp inst="t17980523-19-crimeloc100" type="placeName" value="Saracen's-head, Friday-street"></interp>
                  <interp inst="t17980523-19-crimeloc100" type="type" value="crimeLocation"></interp>
                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t17980523-19-off97 t17980523-19-crimeloc100"></join>, their names are 
               <persName id="t17980523-19-person209">
                  John
                   Whitmarsh
               <interp inst="t17980523-19-person209" type="surname" value="Whitmarsh"></interp>
                     <interp inst="t17980523-19-person209" type="given" value="John"></interp>
